, Somme, Picardie, France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Roucy","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Altered form of German   Rauch  .","French (southern): regional variant of   Rouge   ‘red’.","English (of Norman origin): probably a variant of   Roach  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Rauch","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Otto, Helmut, Kurt, Erwin, Franz, Hans, Heinz, Horst, Wilfried, Angelika, Dieter, Elke.","German, Swiss German, and Jewish (Ashkenazic):","variant of   Rau  ."]}]},{"name":"Louis","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["name, of Germanic (Frankish) origin, from <i>hlōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>wīg</i> ‘war’. It was very common in French royal and noble families.  Louis I  (  778–840 ) was the son of Charlemagne, who ruled as both King of France and Holy Roman Emperor. Altogether, the name was borne by sixteen kings of France up to the French Revolution, in which Louis XVI perished. Louis XIV, ‘the Sun King’ (  1638–1715 ), reigned for seventy-two years (  1643–1715 ), presiding in the middle part of his reign over a period of unparalleled French power and prosperity. In modern times Louis is also found in the English-speaking world (usually pronounced ‘<b>loo</b>-ee’). In Britain the Anglicized form   Lewis   is rather more common, whereas in America the reverse is true."],"variants":[{"name":"Lewie","meanings":["Anglicized spelling of   Louis  , or a pet form of   Lewis ."]},{"name":"Louie","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Lewie   or   Louis  , currently in fashion."]},{"name":"Lewi","meanings":["form, since the Middle Ages, of the French name   Louis .  In modern use it is also in part a transferred use of the surname derived from this given name, or from Anglicized forms of Gaelic <i>Mac Lughaidh</i> ‘son of  <b>Lughaidh</b> ’  or Welsh Llewelyn ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Louis de Roucy was born in 1161. He married Eléonore de Corbie. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died in 1229, at the age of 68."},"et":{"1161–1229":"1161–1229","1164–1208":"1164–1208","1188–1228":"1188–1228","1228":"1228","1188":"1188","1164":"1164","1161":"1161","1208":"1208","1229":"1229","Montdidier, Somme, Picardie, France":"Montdidier, Somme, Picardie, Prantsusmaa","Mailly-Raineval, Somme, Picardie, France":"Mailly-Raineval, Somme, Picardie, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1161–1229":"1161–1229","1164–1208":"1164–1208","1188–1228":"1188–1228","1228":"1228","1188":"1188","1164":"1164","1161":"1161","1208":"1208","1229":"1229","Montdidier, Somme, Picardie, France":"Montdidier, Somme, Picardie, Ranska","Mailly-Raineval, Somme, Picardie, France":"Mailly-Raineval, Somme, Picardie, Ranska"},"fr":{"1161–1229":"1161–1229","1164–1208":"1164–1208","1188–1228":"1188–1228","1228":"1228","1188":"1188","1164":"1164","1161":"1161","1208":"1208","1229":"1229","Montdidier, Somme, Picardie, France":"Montdidier, Somme, Picardie, France","Mailly-Raineval, Somme, Picardie, France":"Mailly-Raineval, Somme, Picardie, France","lifeSummary":"Louis de Roucy est né en 1161. Il a épousé Eléonore de Corbie. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille. Il est décédé en 1229, à l’âge de 68 ans."},"de":{"1161–1229":"1161–1229","1164–1208":"1164–120